<DATE>951127</DATE>
<HEADLINE>20 evacuated in flats blaze</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975175696</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TWENTY people were evacuated from flats in a four-storey building which caught
fire in South Bridge, Edinburgh, last night.
Eight fire engines brought the outbreak under control after more than an hour.
The blaze was in a basement of the building which is part shops and part
residential.
A fire also caused damage at Thomas Muir High School, Wester Cleddans,
Bishopbriggs, Glasgow. The school will be closed today and parents have been
advised to telephone the school on 0141 762 3110 for the re-opening date.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
