<TEXT>
today.
CALUM Macdonald, cox of the Stornoway lifeboat, features in a new video
available this week as part of a marketing campaign being held by the Royal
National Lifeboat Institution to counteract a downturn in its income from
legacies.
Real trier
A STUDENT who lost an arm in a road crash 13 months ago scored three tries at
the weekend in his first rugby match since the accident. Danny Crates, 22,
helped his team, Thurrock Fourth 15 from Essex, beat Gravesend Fourths 42-7 in
a friendly. Crates said: ``I can catch with one hand. I can hold a ball in one
hand. One of my party tricks is holding two pint glasses in one hand.''
Vandal attack
VANDALS caused extensive damage at Borders College of Agriculture at Newtown St
Boswells when they flooded classrooms and offices after putting a hosepipe
through a letterbox. They also destroyed fencing round seedbeds, plastic
coverings on horticultural tunnels, and trays of seeds.
</TEXT>
