<HEADLINE>Worker killed as wall collapses</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975175707</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
POLICE and safety officials are investigating a wall collapse in which one
worker died and another was injured at the ICI site at Cargenbridge near
Dumfries.
The collapse killed Luke Ashford, 19, of Chester. His workmate, Anthony Rees,
46, of Essex, suffered back and knee injuries.
They were part of a contractor's squad which was demolishing a building at the
Melinex One site on Saturday. The two men became trapped under rubble when the
wall collapsed and brought down part of the roof.
Emergency services, including more than 20 firefighters, began removing the
bricks and debris by hand. Mr Rees was quickly freed from the rubble and
admitted to Dumfries Infirmary.
Another worker was taken to the hospital suffering from shock but was released
after examination. It was hours before workers were able to free the dead man
from the debris.
Building control officials from Dumfries and Galloway regional council visited
the scene and the Health and Safety Executive were informed.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
