<HEADLINE>No answer to the Dundee passion</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>By ARTHUR SHORT</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975175716</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DUNDEE soccerites obviously had Hampden in mind but the rugby fanatics were at
Mayfield as High School confirmed their second division status next season.
The comprehensive victory over West made sure of that. It was all about
motivation and the scoreline in that sector was Dundee a lot, West none.
It was difficult for West to put everything into the game, they already knew
they were safe. But pride is still a powerful ally and West coach Sandy Service
felt his boys did not display as much of that ingredient as he would have hoped.
One big difference between the sides was at fly-half. Chris Robinson and David
Barrett both wore the No.10 jersey, but any similarity ended there.
Dundee's Kiwi controlled the match and collected a personal tally of 21 points.
Barrett got off to a bad start by putting the kick-off straight into touch when
an effort straight down the park might have put Dundee under pressure. Instead
the home side snatched a simple three minute try from Sean Longstaff and never
looked back. Robinson converted.
Paul Rouse careered over for an unconverted try in 29 minutes, then, just after
the interval, Robinson extended the lead with a penalty.
In 53 minutes, the fly-half made it 18-0 with another penalty then he helped
himself to a try, a conversion, then penalty No.3. He kept his best kick until
the seventy-second minute when he slotted a cracker from well out on the right
touchline.
Only two minutes remained when Dundee finished it off with a slick try from
McWhirter. It was all over and the Dundee leaps of joy reflected the released
tension.
Dundee HS FP - S Pearson; D Mason, P Rouse, D Hamilton, S Longstaff; C
Robinson, A Featherstone; S Lithgow, G Scott, N Robertson, G Hayter, S
Campbell, C Samson, T McWhirter, D Milne. Replacements - G Sandford for
Featherstone (38min); R Gray for Hayter (41).
West of Scotland - T Greenshield; D Riding, A Bulloch, D McKee, J Craig; D
Barrett, F Stott; S McGregor, G Bulloch, D Jamieson, S McKechnie, G Perrett, D
McLeish, J Lonergan, J Shaw. Replacement - C Dunn for Craig (18).
Referee - C Henderson (Kelso).
SCORERS: Dundee HS FP - Robinson, 1t, 4p, 2c; Rouse, 1t; Longstaff, 1t;
McWhirter 1t.
Dundee HS FP 36,
West of Scotland 0
</TEXT>
