<HEADLINE>Nuclear-free crusade begun</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Illustration</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975175725</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AUSTRALIAN Prime Minister Paul Keating has launched his crusade to rid the
world of nuclear weapons.
The 15-member Canberra Commission, which will report in August, includes former
French premier Michel Rocard, former US defence secretary Robert McNamara, and
Britons General Sir Michael Carver, and Nobel Peace Prize winner Joseph
Rotblat.
``The end of the Cold War means that we can seriously envisage a concrete
programme to achieve a world free of nuclear weapons,'' said Keating.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
