<HEADLINE>Kelso finish with a killer touch of style</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975175726</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
KELSO ensured they would still be playing Division Two rugby next season with
an emphatic win over relegated Stewart's Melville at Poynder Park. It was a
relieved Eric Paxton who watched his team put the luckless Colleges to the
sword.
The Borderers' earlier encounter with Stewart's Melville was the first in a run
of victories which brought them out of the doldrums, and on Saturday they
quickly set about making Colleges the only side to lose to them twice.
Kelso's opening passage of play set the scene - their back row making deep
inroads into the Stewart's Melville defence.
Stuart Bennet's commitment brought him an early head injury but within seconds
of his return to the field, the Kelso captain took a clean lineout catch and
sprinted through a bemused defence for the first try. Graeme Aitchison added
the conversion to his opening penalty goal.
Kelso maintained their pressure and their back row combined well for Bennet to
send in Adam Roxburgh for a try at the corner. The flanker underlined his fine
display with a second touchdown as he backed up a break by Aitchison. The full
back converted and, with a second penalty goal on the stroke of half-time, gave
Kelso a 25-0 lead.
Midway through the second half, Kelso struck again, John Jeffrey scoring at the
posts off good lineout provision from his pack. Aitchison, having slotted a
third penalty goal, added the goal points to Jeffrey's try and Kelso were out
of sight.
They weren't quite finished, however, for, with six minutes to go, replacement
lock Alasdair Stewart celebrated his return to first-class rugby after a
three-year break by scoring the final try.
Kelso - G Aitchison; S Ross, G Laing, B Manion, J Thomson; S Tait, I Fairley; J
Ramage, K Thomson, R Hogarth, S Rowley, C Meade, S Bennet, J Jeffrey, A
Roxburgh. Replacement - A Stewart for Meade (53min).
Stewart's Melville - M Thomson; A Hewit, N Gallagherd, F Pollock, G Stirling; D
Wylie, M Rennie; R McNulty, A Cadzow, J Conlin, M Paton, W Faulds, B Foster, D
Clark, N Penny. Replacement - F Calder for Foster (9).
Referee - L D Crerar (GHK).
SCORERS: Kelso - Roxburgh, 2t; Bennet, 1t; Jeffrey, 1t; Stewart, 1t; Aitchison,
3p, 3c.
Kelso 40,
Stewart's Melville FP 0
</TEXT>
