<TEXT>
THE confusing incident towards the end of the match between Scotland and
Western Samoa indicates the need for a new rule about which I have written
previously. Again, I propose that penalty kicks for illegal offences (i.e.
against the person) as opposed to technical offences, should be taken from a
designated penalty spot no matter on which part of the pitch the offence has
taken place.
The same rule could be considered for all team sports.
Dr John A J Macleod,
``Tigh-na-Hearradh'',
Lochmaddy,
Isle of North Uist,
Western Isles.
</TEXT>
